{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1ebff450-83e4-4c30-ba40-0f3b32e0fb43","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+**, but here's the problem:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET 5 is out of support and MSTest v3 targets `net6.0` as the minimum modern TFM.\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — ❌ Not supported. .NET Core 3.1 is below the minimum.\n- **`net462`** — ✅ Supported (.NET Framework 4.6.2 meets the minimum).\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. Replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or newer, e.g. `net8.0`)\n2. Drop or upgrade `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0`+\n3. Replace the individual package references with the unified `MSTest` meta-package (v3+):\n\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\nThis replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25b70caa-dd9c-49da-90fc-b6830b0fd315","outputTokens":297,"requestId":"EC06:2461FB:66C29F2:6F38B0C:6A034C1E"},"id":"33a7c5e2-3fce-4e97-aace-d93ee23a5741","timestamp":"2026-05-12T15:49:58.374Z","parentId":"40baeba4-4b49-4910-8993-739e776be97b"}
